    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-08T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-08T06:00:00-05:00" n="625"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">783.02/12–851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Syria</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CHB1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d625fn1">Repeated to Paris, London, Ankara, Arab capitals,
                        Tel Aviv, Jerusalem, and Tripoli.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Damascus</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-08T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 8, 1951—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>344. We appreciate Dept’s instructions re recognition new Syrian regime (<gloss
                        target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 312 [<hi rend="italic">212</hi>],
                    December 6)<note n="2" xml:id="d625fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1086">p. 1086</ref>.</note>
                    and fully endorse line of action set forth. We believe acknowledgement of
                    circular not best means effecting recognition, particularly because it can be
                    easily concerted with other western powers and wld avoid previous situations
                    when French tried steal show.</p>
                <p>Today Asst Army Attaché talked briefly to <persName corresp="#p_SCA1"
                        >Shishikli</persName> who after brief résumé recent events said “next move
                    is up to you”. With indications that Arab states may shortly act to recognize
                    regime we think immed agreement with British, French and Turks on Dept’s line of
                    action including draft reply to <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> note
                    highly desirable.<note n="3" xml:id="d625fn3">In response, the Department of
                        State in telegram 228 to Damascus, December 11, instructed the Legation,
                        subject to agreement by the French, British, and Turkish Ministers in
                        Damascus, to join with them in drafting a simple note acknowledging the
                        Syrian note of December 3, which would constitute recognition of the new
                        Syrian Government (783.02/12–851).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CHB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
